biting in its circumstellar\nhabitable zone, becoming the oldest potentially habitable planet known to date.\nThe presence and long-term survival of a planetary system seems a remarkable\nfeat given the peculiar origin and kinematic history of Kapteyn's star. The\ndetection of super-Earth mass planets around halo stars provides important\ninsights into planet-formation processes in the early days of the Milky Way.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Jun 2014 19:18:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-06-06"}
