 lower orbital eccentricities\nthan those orbiting solar-type stars, which suggests that they are either\nformed in different conditions or that their orbits are efficiently\ncircularized by interactions with the host star.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Jun 2014 21:31:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
